 194:         """
 195:         For every item the cosine similarity against other items depends on whether they have users in common. The more
 196:         common users the higher the similarity.
 197:         
 198:         The basic implementation is:
 199:         - Select the first item
 200:         - Loop through all other items
 201:         -- Given the two items, get the users they have in common
 202:         -- Update the similarity for all common users
 203:         
 204:         That is VERY slow due to the common user part, in which a long data structure is looped multiple times.
